Patient walked into the observation area around 5:16pm after his vaccination. He was with his stepfather. He was with normal mentation, walking on his own, and talking with his stepfather in the waiting room. Within 1-2 minutes in the waiting room, he leaned to the right in his chair, hit the glass (glass did not crack or shatter, no head injury), and was not responsive for about 5 seconds. His father called his name and grabbed his hand but no response. I rushed over and patient became responsive and endorses not remembering what happened.  He does not remember the event. No body shaking, tongue biting, or incontinence.  He was taken back to the vital room, and his first BP was 70/35, pulse in the 60s. He denied any symptoms, and physical exam including neurological exam were normal. He was speaking coherently and with good mentation.  He was given a water to drink. Repeat blood pressure 5 minutes later improved to 96/59 with no medication.  He was moved to a clinic room and was laid supine with his legs elevated.  Orthostatic blood pressures were within normal limits (111/63 supine, 110/72 sitting, 109/69 standing). Patient was able to walk out on his own and was in normal mentation.  No medications were given or interventions wee done.

On Sunday, 04/18, I went and received my second dose of the Pfizer vaccine at 12:30 pm on my left arm. It hurt much sooner than the first, within a couple hours. It hurt worse as well. The next morning was Monday. My arm was super sore. I work from home and went by my normal routine. Oatmeal with raspberries and blueberries.  I eat this every day. I started work at 9 AM. Around 9:30 Am or so, I started having sneezing fits. Which I thought was annoying more than anything, but didn't think anything of it, until the fits developed into my hands itching, burning, turning red. I looked at my face and noticed it was red and swelling.  I've had skin allergies before, but nothing outside of hives and maybe a little skin swelling.  I have an allergy to bees. Worse that ever occurred was hives. This instance did not produce hives but a very beet red rash and swelling.  Then very quickly after, my tongue started swelling and my throat started tightening. I called my mother as I noted this was life threatening and went to the ER. I was informed I had experienced anaphylaxis.  My heart rate going in to the ER was 166. I have never experienced this in the 32 years I've lived before.  I was administered an Epi and steroids. As soon as I realized what it was, even in my panic, I was lucky to make a judgment call to save my life. The doctor said to throw out the berries just in case. The odd thing is, I eat this every day...no issues. I realize it is rare for reactions to be delayed, but was made aware it is possible.  I was not stung by anything to make this occur.
LAB_DATA: ER visit so no tests. Just treatment.  EpiPen and steroids.  I also have to be on a 5 day steroid regimen with 2 spare EpiPens for the future.  I did not have one before as I never experienced anaphylaxis in the past. Nothing benadryl couldn't fix.
ALLERGIES: Bee allergies. Skin only. Hives. Rash.

I received the shot on 4/10. First 24 hours I had a slight fever and headache. Treated with Acetaninophhen. Since that time, I had relatively mild symptoms 4/11 - 4/13. Mostly fatigue.  On 4/14, I had a sudden increase in heart rate, dizziness, tingling sensation in all arms and legs and weakness in my limbs/grip. This prompted me to visit the ER. They ran numerous blood tests amd scans on me but found no abnormalities. Various unusual symptoms have continued to persist since 4/14.  For brief moments I feel fine.  At other times I have experience fatigue, diziness/vertigo, rapid heart rate, pins and needles feeling in my left hand and left leg.  Left leg numbness/tightness and heaviness. The fingers on my left hand sometimes move involuntarily.  And my anxiety has also gone up during this time. Tonight it has migratee to my left foot, where I have numbness in several of my toes.  I'm looking for advice. Should I be concerned? Should these symptoms still be occurring 11 days after receiving my shot?  It has been very distressing and there seem to be very few people who have knowledge on this subject.  My care providers keep saying to self monitor and contact them if symptoms worsen. The problem is symptoms don't necessarily worsen, they just migrate from one area of my body to another.  The numbness comes and goes in maybe 1-2 hour intervals.
LAB_DATA: I would have to check over my ER visit records.  They took multiple blood tests and tested urine.  EKG monitor. Lung scan. MRI on my brain. Keeping in mind that this was all within hours of my initial adverse reaction.  From my understanding, all tests returned fairly normal results for a healthy 43 y/o male, so they were not immediately concerned that this was vaccine related.  But my sysmptoms persist off and on and it has been a full week since the initial reaction.
HISTORY: Slight tinitus. Some toenail fungus. Nothing serious

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 3/17/2021, I began to have a very heavy mentrual period and it was 5 days early (which never happens). On 3/22/21 I had a nose bleed at work, which also never happens. I got home from work at an RN and took off my compression stocking and had bad petechiae all over my lower extremities and scattered throughout my body. I immediately went to the Emergency Room. My labs at the ER showed my platelets were 2000! Normal platelets are over 150,000. They admitted my for thrombocytopenia and I was hospitalized for 12 nights. I was given platelets, high doses of prednisone, IVIG infusions 8 times, rituximab infusion 4 times, bone marrow biopsy which was negative, and nplate injections. Since discharge, I have been seeing the hematology team 3 times a week at facility, labs 3 times a week, rituximab infusion every friday, nplate injection once a week. I have not been able to work since 3/22/21. My diagnosis is an autoimmune response called idiopathic thrombocytopenia.
LAB_DATA: Platelets  and CBC daily from 3/22/21-4/2/21. Bone Marrow Biopsy on 3/26/21. CT scan chest and abdomen 3/24/21. US Abdomen 3/27/21. During hospitalization, platelets range from less than 2000-21,000.

Unusual bouts of shortness of breath lasting between 5 minutes and one hour. Tightness in the chest. Typically, before being vaccinated, I only used my rescue inhaler a few times a month, but I?ve had to use it four times a day since the symptoms started after I received the second dose of the covid vaccine. Three days ago I even went to immediate care to get tested for Covid, got an x-ray of my lungs and an EKG, but all the results were normal. My oxygen level is 98, but the bouts of shortness of breath and tightness in the chest  continue to occur a few times a day, and during those episodes i feel like I cannot get a good breath even though my oxygen level remains high. Between these bouts, I feel fine. The doctors that met with me in the immediate care clinic thought this is likely a reaction to the Pfizer covid 19 vaccine, since all the tests came back normal. I have and echocardiogram and a chest CT scheduled in early May, but I will try to get these tests sooner.  I do not have the typical side effects of the vaccine, such as fever, body aches, headache or nausea. I do not have rashes or swelling of lymph nodes. Episodes of shortness of breath that are sometimes accompanied by tightness in my chest are my only symptoms. I have had COPD and asthma for decades, and these bouts feel different to me. My rescue inhaler does not always work when one of these episodes happens. I am not having difficulty walking or climbing stairs, except during one of these attacks. On the average i experience between two to four of these episodes per day.
LAB_DATA: Covid and Flu Test (result: negative), Chest x-ray (result: normal with no sign of pneumonia), EKG (normal).

Summary: between 12-26 hours after shot, flu-like symptoms. 4 rounds of vomiting + headache.  Monday night ~10:00 p.m.: random, mild pain in chest; feels like a needle is poking into my heart. More wiped out than usual, go to bed 1-2 hours earlier than normal. Monday night-Tuesday morning, ~12 hours after shot: ~1:40 a.m. Wake up with chills & apparent fever; didn't have thermometer ~2:02 a.m. Nausea quickly turns to vomiting. Headache begins. ~3:30 a.m. 2nd round of vomiting. Dry heaves. Muscle contractions are longer & more severe than typical for me. ***Unable to sleep much. Fever apparently breaks. Headache, overall fatigue.*** ~7:30 a.m. 3rd round of vomiting. Dry heaves. Muscle contractions are longer & more severe than typical for me. ~10:00-10:30 a.m. Drive to pharmacy; buy thermometer and aspirin. Thermometer reads 97.4�, then 96.7�, so the fever is long gone. ~11:00-12:30 p.m. Take one tablet (81 mg) of aspirin every 30 minutes with a couple of ounces of water. That's all the water I can drink. ~12:40 p.m. 4th round of vomiting; lost the water. Muscle contractions wouldn't stop; I felt dizzy at the end. ~2:10 p.m. Wake up feeling slightly better; last 30 minutes on the computer for work. Go back to sleep. ~4:15 p.m. Wake up feeling much better; last ~1 hour on the computer. ~10:00 p.m. start eating again. First time in 24 hours.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Monday night pt. became ill, threw up and had a fever.  He went to bed, but around 11 pm he woke up disoriented, unable to walk.  Was helped to the bathroom, but was unable to get back to bed on his own.  Fell on his bottom.  I had to call our son to come pick him up and help him back to bed, unable to hold his own weight..  Had trouble sleeping.  Abt 1 pm needed help getting up again, same disorientation, also fell off the toilet and needed help getting back to the bed, unable to hold his own weight.  Finally fell asleep.  Next day seemed fine enough. Tuesday night, became ill again, went to bed.  Got up to go to the bathroom, was wobbly, but able to make it.  Was helped back, wobbly but able to walk. Trouble falling asleep, fever, chills.  Finally fell asleep at 3 am Wed morning.  I had to go to the doctor early, so left him sleeping in bed.  When I came back around 11 am, he was still sleeping, snoring loudly.  Became concerned.  Wouldn't wake up.  Called Paramedics.  CT scan at the hospital revealed a brain bleed.  Transported to hospital. Put on support for almost 2 weeks.  No progress, no response.  Finally support was discontinued and he died April 19th at 7:52 pm.
LAB_DATA: CT Scans daily April 7 - 18 MRI (about April 13) EEG (abt April 13) Labs and other test in hospital records, I don't know them.

herpes zoster/blisters on left side of torso, back and spine; This initial spontaneous report was received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation concerning to a patient of unknown age and gender. Information regarding medical history, concurrent conditions and concomitant medications was not provided. On 09-OCT-2017, the patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (dosage regimen, route of administration, lot number and expiration date were not reported) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). On an unknown date, subsequently after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered blisters on left side of torso, back and spine and was diagnosed with Herpes Zoster. As a result of these symptoms, the patient was seen and treated by medical providers. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient's symptoms resulted in physical limitations were not present prior to using zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of patient's condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries. The outcome of the event of shingles was considered as not recovered. The reporter considered the events to be related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).  Upon internal review, the event of shingles was considered to be disabling event.

shortness of breath/ chest pain/ burning throat and SOB/ diagnosed as allergic reaction or possible asthma flare; shortness of breath/ chest pain/ burning throat and SOB/ diagnosed as allergic reaction or possible asthma flare; overwhelming fatigue; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer, based on information received by Pfizer(manufacturer control number: US-AMGEN-USASP2021052927), license party for etanercept (ENBREL).  This non-serious spontaneous report (USASP2021052927) was reported on 06/APR/2021 by a consumer and involves a 29 year old female patient who experienced had shortness of breath/ chest pain/ burning throat and SOB/ diagnosed as allergic reaction or possible asthma flare [PT: hypersensitivity] while receiving Enbrel with Single Dose Prefilled Syringe and Aimovig with Single Dose Prefilled Autoinjector. No historical medical condition was reported. The patient's current medical condition included psoriatic arthritis, migraine, and asthma. No concomitant medications were provided. The patient's co-suspect medication included Covid-19 Vaccine. The patient began Aimovig with Single Dose Prefilled Autoinjector on an unknown date in JUL/2018. The patient started taking Enbrel with Single Dose Prefilled Syringe on an unknown date in 2020. On 15/MAR/2021, the patient received her first Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination. On 25/MAR/2021, the patient took her latest Enbrel injection. On 27/MAR/2021, the patient took her latest Aimovig injection. On 28/MAR/2021, Sunday, the patient started experiencing shortness of breath (SOB) and chest pain which lead her to see her physician the following Monday. On 29/MAR/2021, the patient performed electrocardiogram (ECG) at the physician's office which was normal. On 29/MAR/2021, on Monday night, the patient went to the emergency room with a burning throat and SOB and the patient was diagnosed with an allergic reaction or possible asthma flare, and she was prescribed a prednisone taper which she did not take and baclofen. The patient had been taking the baclofen and using her Xopenex (levosalbutamol hydrochloride) rescue inhaler as needed for SOB. The patient also reported that the SOB and chest pain was getting better but still had issues. On an unknown date in 2021, the patient also reported that she had been experiencing overwhelming fatigue and was scheduled to receive her second Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination on 09/APR/2021. The outcome of the events hypersensitivity was reported as unknown. Action taken with Enbrel and Single Dose Prefilled Syringe was reported as unknown for the events hypersensitivity. Action taken with Aimovig with Single Dose Prefilled Autoinjector was reported as unknown for the events hypersensitivity. The causal relationship between the events hypersensitivity, and Enbrel with Single Dose Prefilled Syringe was not provided by the consumer. The causal relationship between the events hypersensitivity and Aimovig with Single Dose Prefilled Autoinjector was not provided by the consumer. Follow up is not required.

Spent 2 days in bed with a 100.5 fever ( normal is 97.6); Extreme fatigue / my fatigue was more than normal for me; Developed pronounced brain fog which was previously not pronounced; Very apathetic/ il motivated; Experience a sore / arm for 5 days; Experience a / swollen arm for 5 days; Spent 2 days in bed; This case was reported by a consumer and described the occurrence of pain in arm in a adult patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Concurrent medical conditions included fibromyalgia.   On an unknown date, the patient received Shingrix. On an unknown date, unknown after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced pain in arm, swelling arm, activities of daily living impaired, fever, fatigue, foggy feeling in head and apathy. On an unknown date, the outcome of the pain in arm, swelling arm and activities of daily living impaired were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the fever and apathy were unknown and the outcome of the fatigue and foggy feeling in head were not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the pain in arm, swelling arm, activities of daily living impaired, fever, fatigue, foggy feeling in head and apathy to be related to Shingrix.   Additional details were provided as follows: This case was reported by patient himself/herself. The age group was not reported but was selected as an adult as per vaccine indication. The age at vaccination was not reported. The patient received both doses of Shingrix and experienced a sore and swollen arm for 5 days and spent 2 days in bed with a 100.5 degree F fever and had extreme fatigue for 4 days. The patient stated that he/she had fibromyalgia, so every side effect and symptom was magnified and lasts longer, so his/her fatigue was more than normal for him/her and on the scale of 1 to 10, 10 being extreme, the patient went from 4 to 8 and the patient also developed pronounced brain fog which was previously not pronounced and on same 1 to 10 scale, the patient went from a 2 to 8. The patient stated that all of this pronounced fatigue and brain fog lasted about 10 days and though the levels dropped, 3 plus weeks later, his/her fatigue and brain fog level was about 5. The patient noticed that he/she was suddenly very apathetic and in motivated. The patient asked if there had been any other reports with similar effects. The patient stated that he/she trying to resolve his/her extra fatigue and brain fog, apathy and lack of motivation and was looking for answers.  The patient had no other illness, clinical depression and any issues with his/her family. Felt like COVID symptoms / from when she had COVID in September 2020; Redness / at the injection site / second dose was worse; Swelling / at the injection site / second dose was worse; Pain at the injection site / second dose was worse; Arm was very / hot /  like fever in her arm at the injection site; Arm was very sore; Arm was very / red; Fever elevated fast from 99 to 100.5; Headache; Myalgia in her back, shoulders and lower back; Fatigued with a headache; Had to lay down; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of suspected covid-19 in a 64-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included covid-19 (in September 2020). Previously administered products included Shingrix with an associated reaction of injection site pain (1st dose received October or November 2020 (actual date was not confirmed), for tolerance refer case US2021AMR007263).   On 7th January 2021, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On 8th January 2021, 1 days after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced injection site erythema, injection site swelling, injection site pain, injection site warmth, pain in arm, erythema of extremities, fever, headache, myalgia, fatigue and activities of daily living impaired. On an unknown date, the patient experienced suspected covid-19. The patient was treated with paracetamol (Tylenol). Rechallenge with Shingrix was positive. On an unknown date, the outcome of the injection site erythema, injection site swelling, injection site pain, injection site warmth, pain in arm, erythema of extremities, headache, myalgia, fatigue and activities of daily living impaired were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the fever and suspected covid-19 were unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the injection site erythema, injection site swelling, injection site pain, injection site warmth, pain in arm, erythema of extremities, fever, headache, myalgia, fatigue, activities of daily living impaired and suspected covid-19 to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were reported as follows: The patient received Shingrix and her symptoms came on very quickly and were severe. She had redness, swelling and pain at the injection site. The second dose was worse.  Her arm was very sore, red and hot like she had a fever in her arm at the injection site for the second dose.  Her fever elevated fast from 99 to 100.5 and she had a headache and myalgia in her back, shoulders and lower back.  She was fatigued with a headache.  Her symptoms started 4 hours after vaccination, but all of the symptoms had resolved at the time of reporting.  She also claimed that she received the second dose of Shingrix on 7th January 2021 and her symptoms from the second dose actually started on Friday 8th January 2021, around 4 to 5:00 pm. She felt better by bed time but she did take Tylenol. She claimed that she was told by the Pharmacist to get her second dose of Shingrix two months after the first dose and they gave her a date of 28th December 2020 to return for the second dose. She waited past that date but got the second dose either in October or November 2020 but she could not confirm the actual date of the vaccination. She had to lay down and she claims that it felt like COVID symptoms from when she had COVID in September 2020.  Consented to follow up.   Reporting error received for this case and following correction was done: Re-challenge result was added in event screen for all events.; Sender's Comments:  US-GLAXOSMITHKLINE-US2021AMR007263:Same reporter

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PT MENTIONED SHE WAS NERVOUS ABOUT GETTING THE SHOT.  AFTER SHE RECEIVED THE SHOT, SHE WENT INTO THE WAITING ROOM AND A FEW MINS LATER, FELT LIKE SHE WAS GOING TO PASS OUT. WE HAD HER LAY ON THE FLOOR AND ELEVATED HER FEET.  SHE PROCEEDED TO PASS OUT.  WE ADMINISTERED THE SMELLING SALTS, SHE WAS SLIGHTLY AWAKE BUT OUT OF IT AND SAID SHE DIDN'T SMELL ANYTHING.  WE LIFTED HER MASK AND DID ANOTHER SMELLING SALT AND SHE "WOKE UP" BUT STILL REMAINDED ON THE FLOOR. SHE FELT WEIRD, EYES REMAINDED CLOSED AND SHE WAS SLIGHTLY CRYING AN SCARED.  WE ASKED HER PARTNER IF THIS HAS EVERY HAPPENED BEFORE AND HE SAID SHE HAS ONLY PASSED OUT B/C OF PAIN NOT ANXIETY.  WE TOOK HER PRESSURE/HEART RATE EVERY 5 MIN FOR 15 MIN.  IT WAS ELEVATED 165/110 (HR 69) AND STAYED AROUND THAT EACH READING.  WE ASKED HER IF SHE WANTED US TO CALL EMT AFTER THE FIRST 5-10 MIN AND SHE WASN'T SURE.  15-20 MIN LATER WE CALLED EMT AND THEY CAME TO ASSIST.  THEY TOOK HER VITALS AND THEN EVENTUALLY HELPED HER SIT UP AND EVENTUALLY SHE WALKED OUT ON HER OWN.

The patient did not have vericose veins. No allergies were reported.  The patient received vaccination with JANSSEN COVID-19 VACCINE (covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s) (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 206A217, expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, 1 total, administered on right deltoid muscle on 11-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. No concomitant medications were reported as it was reported that patient did not take any medications.  On 11-APR-2021, the patient received the vaccine and within 3 minutes, she felt dizzy and fainted and was taken by Emergency Medical Services to a hospital. Her vital signs were taken (pulse rate, blood pressure, and oxygen saturation) and patient was found to be hypotensive (the husband did not recall blood pressure level). When blood sugar was being tested using a needle for a prick, the blood was not coming out. Her blood sugar was normal at 129 and electrocardiogram was normal. The patient was given intravenous fluids and released home after 6 hours without any other treatment. The patient has been doing well since the release from the hospital ED and no further complaints were reported.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from fainted and blood pressure was low on 11-APR-2021. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0: The case concerns a 31-year -old female who experienced low blood pressure 3-4 minutes after Janssen Covid-19 vaccine was administered intramuscularly for prevention of symptomatic SARS-CoV-2 virus infection. Patient's height and weight were not reported. Medical history included resolved gestational diabetes. The patient had no history of allergic reactions or reactions to a flu vaccine (last one received OCT-2020). No concomitant medications. Post vaccination the patient felt dizzy, could not sit on the chair and fainted and was taken to Emergency Room.  Her blood pressure was low and she experienced hot flashes and watery eyes. Her blood sugar was 129 and electrocardiogram was normal. The subject was given IV infusion and was released from the ED without any medication. Symptoms of low blood pressure and fainting are known anxiety related reactions to immunization and given temporal relationship are considered likely related  to Janssen vaccine administration.

GUILLAIN BARRE SYNDROME; This spontaneous report received from a consumer concerned a 62 year old male. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's concurrent medical history included diabetes. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 1805025, and expiry: 25-MAY-2021) dose was not reported, administered on 12-MAR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included insulin for diabetes. The patient was in Critical Care unit. On Saturday, the next day after the vaccine, the patient was not felling well in afternoon and had laid down for few hours. They had a trip scheduled for Sunday. The patient was feeling well when he left home on Sunday. By Friday, 19-MAR-2021 (a week from the day he got his vaccine), he started with leg and knee pain. On 20-MAR-2021, the pain moved up to his back and then into his shoulders. The patient arrived home on Friday, 19-MAR-2021 and at 9:30 pm that night the patient woke up and could not handle the severe pain. On 20-MAR-2021, the patient was admitted to emergency room to ensure it was not heart related. The patient had a spinal trap on Saturday and by Sunday/Monday the patient found out it was Guillain barre syndrome. The patient was not able to walk and had also lost feeling from the neck down and could not move. The reporter had stated, the patient's right side was worse then left so doctors had investigated occurrence of stroke but nothing was found. The patient had episodes where he was unable to speak but was feeling better. He could talk and communicate better, but was limited and could not write. The doctors were working on getting the patient strong enough for rehab. The patient wife had stated that the recovery expected to be a long process. The patient wife also stated that patient was not on ventilator.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient had not recovered from Guillain barre syndrome. This report was serious (Hospitalization Caused / Prolonged, Life Threatening, and Disability Or Permanent Damage).; Sender's Comments: V0: A 62-year-old white male experienced Guillain-Barre Syndrome (GBS) 8 or 9 days after vaccine. Medical history included diabetes, for which he took insulin. On day 7 after vaccine, he started with leg and knee pain. On day 8, the pain moved up to his back and then into his shoulders, that night the patient was troubled by worsening pain and presented to emergency room. The patient had a spinal tap that day and within 1-2 days the patient found out it was GBS. The patient was not able to walk and had also lost feeling from the neck down and could not move. The patient's right side was worse than left so doctors had investigated occurrence of stroke but nothing was found. The patient had episodes where he was unable to speak but was feeling better. He could talk and communicate better but was limited and could not write. The doctors were working on getting the patient strong enough for rehab. The patient was not on a ventilator and a long recovery was anticipated. No laboratory results were reported, including those of campylobacter, viral infections, or cerebrospinal fluid analysis. Although there is a close temporal relationship, there is insufficient information to make a meaningful medical assessment. Additional information has been requested, including consent to contact the treating physicians to obtain additional details of clinical care and diagnostics.
LAB_DATA: Test Date: 20210320; Test Name: Spinal tap; Result Unstructured Data: Guillain barre syndrome; Comments: Guillain  Barre Syndrome.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Next morning severe headache to the point of delirium....2nd day a little better...headache gone....fatigue...3rd day still tired..got up in late afternoon....tiredness lasted about 5days

*4/4 Morning felt like I couldn't walk, knew my feet were their, but couldn't register to move for hr and then got up, EXTREME pain in center of my left armpit (to point of almost crying and it was worse than my kidney stone pain I had for a week) and all over pain in body-hard to even move much this day...I slept in 12 hr increments till next day.  Noticed my Heart rate was very high constantly between 100-115 ( on my wrist monitor) * On 4/5 Woke up and told myself to get moving for day, arm was turning very red at this point and swelling bad along with armpit along edge and was hot and still painful. Was up for 7 hr.. I got in shower that evening  and felt weird midway and my head felt like a whoosh and thought I was going to pass out (normal temp in shower) held onto shower got out was fine for about 20 min and then I started extreme shaking uncontrollably and teeth were chattering from chills. Went to get a Tylenol because I knew something was not right and within 30 min started sweating profusely with fever (I didn't even get up because I felt so crappy) *4/6 Woke up, felt a little better, arm, armpit and side of armpit red, hot and swollen still. Was up for 9 hrs, but when I went to bed and laid down, I felt like I couldn't breathe well...something told me to take a deep breath and I felt something like a pop in chest and then I felt like I was breathing better. Was not still feeling good  on 4/7  but went back to work, on 4/8 felt a lot better, then woke 4/9 with Migraine and felt terrible and my heart felt weird...I  called the Health Department and asked what to do and they recommended going to doctor... but a Nurse followed up with me which was very nice. Went to doctor and my Blood Pressure was 179/98 at that time. They ran blood work and prescribed me a antibiotic for my arm and armpit area. I want to add as well, not sure if this matters, but my shot was not in center of arm...it was closer to inner part of upper shoulder closer to chest.
LAB_DATA: 4/9 Doctor checked arm and went ahead and treated it with antibiotic so it didn't go to Cellulitis? Ran Blood work, that came back normal. Thank the Lord.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: BLOODY NOSE; BELL'S PALSY; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 73 year old female patient. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's past medical history included carotid surgery on 12-MAR-2021.  The patient received vaccination with JANSSEN COVID-19 VACCINE (covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s) (suspension for injection, route of admin intramuscular, batch number: 042A21A, expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, administered to left arm on 02-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included clopidogrel bisulfate for blood thinner. The patient reported no other symptoms or side effects after the vaccine.  Around 07-APR-2021, patient started getting Bell's palsy and went to the Emergency Room (ER) because she thought she was having a stroke. The patient was diagnosed with Bell's palsy. The patient followed up with primary care provided on 12-APR-2021. Patient's Bell's palsy was not recovered completely but was almost gone. The patient had bloody nose on 13-APR-2021 and went to urgent care. The patient was told not to worry about it and 'it will probably never happen again'.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from bleeding from nose, and was recovering from bell's palsy. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0: This 73-year-old female patient experienced medically important Bell's palsy 5 days after receiving JANSSEN COVID-19 VACCINE (covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s) intramuscularly to left arm for prophylactic vaccination. The patient's had carotid surgery 21 days prior to the vaccination. Concomitant medications included clopidogrel bisulphate. The patient reported no other symptoms after the vaccination. She started to get Bell's palsy symptoms 5 days post vaccination and visited emergency room. She was diagnosed with Bell's palsy. Details of symptoms, diagnosis, treatment were not reported. She followed up with primary care provider 10 days post vaccination and was seen with Bell's palsy "almost gone". She was recovering from Bell's palsy. The patient experienced non-serious bloody nose the next day and had recovered.  Although information is limited, as there is no confirmatory epidemiologic/biologic evidence that vaccinations cause/contribute to the development of Bell's palsy, and the most common causes include viral infection and diabetes, the event is assessed to have an indeterminate causal association to immunization, per WHO causality classification for adverse events following immunization. Company causality for Bell's Palsy is considered not related to JANSSEN COVID-19 VACCINE.  Additional information has been requested for further assessment.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Arterial operation NOS

SYMPTOM_TEXT: "COVID Arm" - large red rash on arm. Hot to touch, not raised or bumpy. 8 days after injection, lasted 2.5 weeks

I experienced "Moderna Arm" on the day following the injection, but it subsided after a couple of days. Eight days later, though, it returned (swelling/redness/milder pain) -- accompanied by swelling in my right ankle and tightness/some tingling/mild pain in my right ankle/upper calf. I suffered a blood clot for the first time in each leg in early November; the more serious of the two was in the vicinity of my upper calf in my right leg. In December, I began to experience sensations in my right ankle that were similar (albeit more intense) to what I later experienced after my vaccine; the post-vaccination symptom in my right calf was also similar (but milder) to what I had experienced from the DVT.
HISTORY: DVT (as of early November 2020); asymptomatic ITP (as of 1995 or earlier).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Exacerbation of tinnitus. Heightened volume with minor dizziness

Around 6:30 pmI began feeling chills and incredibly tired.  I became sore all over and began shaking uncontrollably because of the chills.  I went to sleep around 7pm and woke up 20 minutes laterwith the worst fever I ever had.  I was extremely hot but when I lifted the covers I would immediately get cold.  I got out of bed around 3am because I was very thirsty and completly stuffed up in my head and sinuses.  I used vicks sinex and drank water and tea.  I was very cold when i got out of bed.  I went back to bed and woke up every 30 mins or so very hot and chilly when I lifted the covers.  I finally got out of bed at 6am.  At that point I had sweated through two shirts, my sheets and comforter.  When i got out of bed I was no longer chilly.  I had a mild headache, sinus pressure and soreness throughout my neck and shoulders.  Throughout the day (April 21, 2021) I would get chills and then get hot.  I continued to havce sinus pressure and a mild headache.  I went to bed around 8:30pm and woke up at 3:00am.  when I woke up I had sweated through half my shirt.  At the time of writing (April 22, 2021 @ 6:08am) I feel slight sinus pressure, no headache and get chills and hot from time to time.
OTHER_MEDS: Lamotrogine, Preponanol, turmeric, vitamin C, fish oil, apple cider vinegar

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Shingles outbreak on face.

Previously healthy 46 yoM received moderna dose 1 on 4/9.  On 4/13 starts noticing a petechial rash on bilateral feet.  This spreads up the legs with some involvement in the torso.  On 4/15 notices mucosal bleeding with gums while brushing teeth, increasing spontaneous nose bleeds overnight.  On 4/21 has a telehealth PCP visit, sent for lab work which shows thrombocytopenia with a platelet count of 2k as well as a hemoglobin of 12.9.  Is sent to the ED with repeat platelet count of 1k.  Previously platelets were 143k  in 2019.  Pt admitted for further work-up

SYMPTOM_TEXT: CEREBRAL INTRACRANIAL HYPERTENSION WITH FREE FLUID IN  BRAIN BEHIND  EYE; FLARED UP ARTHIRITIS; This spontaneous report received from a patient and concerned a 52 year old, White, not Hispanic or Latino, female. Initial information was received on 16-APR-2021 from the patient, with additional information received on 20-APR-2021 from the patient.  The patient's weight was 170 pounds, and height was 65.5 inches. The most recent body mass index was 27.9. The patient's family history included rheumatoid arthritis in father, and concurrent conditions included arthritis (possibly rheumatoid arthritis), chronic back pain, and hip pain. The patient was due for a surgery, but it was cancelled due to pandemic. She had no history of headaches or migraines. Patient received several unspecified vaccines (had several vaccines 3 years ago before trip ) with no problems. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 1805020 expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, administered on 15-MAR-2021 on right arm for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included acetylsalicylic acid 81 mg, daily, ascorbic acid, ergocalciferol, metaxalone, oxycodone, and zinc. The patient concurrently receives spinal/epidural pain injections every two to three months.  Approximately 16-30 hours after the vaccination, she had a flare up of her arthritis (left hip, L3, L4, L5, sciatic pain on the left side going all the way down to her knee, ankle, and foot, where her normal arthritis hurts daily). Pain medication did not help. She also developed migraines which caused pain behind the left eye similar to severe sinus infection, light sensitivity, her face felt tingly and numb in her temples and cheeks (left side). She was concerned about a stroke, but did not have droopiness and could smile on both sides. On 29-MAR-2021 (day 14 post vaccination), the patient went to her pain specialist to receive her spinal/epidural pain injection because she was in a lot of pain and she was "overdue". In retrospect, the patient wondered if she should have waited longer after having received the vaccine before doing so. On 30-MAR-2021 (day 15 post vaccination), she awoke and was blind for several (12 - 14) hours. She thought she had a stroke and took 4 baby aspirins. She was rushed to the hospital and was hospitalized on 30-MAR-2021. After the initial 2-3 hours that she was completely blind, it would come back within minutes. The vision came back in halos. It was blurry but if she moved or bent down, it would go again and then it would come back very quickly. Several tests were performed. The MRI (Magnetic resonance imaging) did not show clots, stroke, or tumors, but showed intracranial hypertension. After the CT and MRI, a lumbar puncture was performed (results not provided). The patient said that the hospital noted cerebral intracranial hypertension with free fluid in her brain behind her eye. In the hospital, bloodwork was normal except for her triglycerides which were high. Patient reported that her platelet levels which were "perfect" and provided "318" as a specific example. She was discharged on 01-APR-2021.  Corrective treatments included: steroids in the hospital for the intracranial hypertension and prescription strength aspirin 325 mg. The patient was not certain if injectable blood thinners were given to her in the hospital. She was discharged with methylprednisolone, alprazolam, twice a day prn to treat her headaches, aspirin 325 mg daily, and rosuvastatin 5 mg, daily, for high triglycerides. After patient was discharged, she had 2 episodes of lightheadedness with the blindness. The first one lasted about 5 minutes maximum and the second one on 12-APR-2021 lasted approximately  30-40 minutes. She had to be sitting down and her vision returned in halos with a lot of fireworks like bright stars. The patient had ringing in the ears, especially the left ear and when she had these episodes. On 14-APR-2021, the patient patient went to PCP (primary care provider). She stated that alprazolam helps her headaches. On 20-APR-2021, she had a "good day", did not experience headaches, and did not take alprazolam. She will follow up with a neurologist and an ophthalmologist. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The outcome of the cerebral intracranial hypertension with free fluid in brain behind eye and flared up arthritis were not reported. This report was serious (Hospitalization Caused / Prolonged, and Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0: This 52 year-old White female was hospitalized for intracranial hypertension 15 days after receiving the Janssen Covid-19 vaccine.  Medical history includes an unspecified arthritis with chronic left hip and back pain for which she receives epidural injections every 2-3 months, and a body mass index of 27.9. She has no history of migraines or other headaches and has tolerated multiple vaccinations previously. Concomitant medications include acetylsalicylic acid 81 mg daily, metaxalone, and oxycodone. Approximately 16 hours after vaccination, she experienced a flare of her arthritis which her pain medications did not relieve. The next day, she began to experience migraine headaches which were associated with pain behind her left eye and sinuses, left-sided facial tingling and numbness without weakness, and light sensitivity.  Fourteen days post-vaccination, she received an epidural injection because she was in a lot of pain. The following morning, she awoke and experienced visual disturbance, described as "complete" blindness. then return of vision with halos and blurriness, and intermittent loss and return of vision depending on her body position. She took 4 baby aspirins, went to the hospital, and was admitted. MRI showed intracranial hypertension but no clots, stroke, or tumors. A lumbar puncture and CT scan were also performed. Blood tests, including platelet counts (e.g. 318), were normal except for high triglycerides. She was treated with steroids and aspirin 325 mg and was discharged 2 days later. She was given methylprednisolone, oxycodone-acetaminophen and alprazolam prn for headaches, aspirin 325 mg, and rosuvatstatin for high triglycerides to continue at home and will follow up with a neurologist, ophthalmologist and her primary physician. Based on the available information, the relationship of intracranial hypertension with Janssen Covid-19 vaccine is considered inconsistent.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PARALYZED LEFT SIDE OF THE BODY; DEATH; This spontaneous report received from a health care professional concerned a 29 year old female. Initial information received on 16-APR-2021, processed along with information received via telephone communication on 20-APR-2021. The patient's weight was estimated about 200 pounds (reported as overweight but healthy). The patient's height and medical history were not reported. The patient had a baby in JAN-2021 and had a epidural at the time of birth.  The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: UNKNOWN) dose, start therapy date were not reported, 1 total for prophylactic vaccination. The vaccination site was not reported. No concomitant medications were reported.  The reporter, which is a health care professional, reported that the patient's (the reporter's cousin) death cause could be JANSSEN COVID-19 vaccine. The reporter said that the patient was fine without symptoms for one week after her scheduled vaccine.  As per the reporter, the patient received the JANSSEN COVID-19 vaccine approximately 2 weeks ago (the patient was scheduled and her family assumed she went and received the vaccine). The reporter said that one week after the vaccine date the patient went to get her hair done, and when the patient sat on the chair, she suddenly could not move her left side. Ambulance/emergency room was called and the patient was taken to the hospital. The patient was in the hospital about a week and then passed away. An autopsy was performed but results were pending. The reporter had no details regarding imaging studies or laboratory values (platelet counts, D-dimer or fibrinogen), and does not know anything about the hospital course. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient died on 16-APR-2021, and the outcome of paralyzed left side of the body was not reported. This report was serious (Death, and Hospitalization Caused / Prolonged).; Sender's Comments: V0:  This is a spontaneous report of a 29-year-old female who developed sudden hemiplegia approximately one week after receiving the Janssen COVID-19 vaccine, was hospitalized and died one week later.  The patient had a history of being overweight, and was approximately 3 months post-partum.  No medical history or concomitant medications were reported.  The hospital details and cause of death were not provided.  There are insufficient details to make a meaningful medical assessment at this time. Additional information has been requested.  The case will be assessed further when additional information is received.; Reported Cause(s) of Death: UNKNOWN CAUSE OF DEATH

10 days after the shot, my blood pressure rose to 198/112 and my pulse went to 161. and i called 911 and went to hospital.  i had a severe headache for 3 days leading up to calling 911. finally on the April 1st, i went to hospital. i had a lump on my right shoulder never there before and i felt like the lump was causing my right side of my face to be numb.  The hospital refused to believe me that i had some blood clot, they downplay the incident and instead gave me a brain CT SACN and brain  MRA which was negative, they kept me for observation overnight and let me go noon the next day.  since i have had follow ups with my regular doctor, a cardiologist and my nephrologist.  I know that reaction was due to medication, either way glad i got the shot.  BUT Since this time, I am retaining water, i know this because my rings do not fit anymore, rings i had for 20 years, never ever once had a hard time to put on or remove. I know my body, thats not the worse of it. i test my blood pressure every day at requesting of my kidney doctor,   since the incudent of my pressure 198/112 my diastolic on average is raised  20 points.  I log this daily.  here are some examples from before the medication  111/67 ,  109/63 ,   129/64 , 105/62 120/81.   now my pressure is totally different for example, 155/88  150/91  157/90 ,  134/88.  nothing else changed in my life, I am exactly the same as before only now i have covid shot..  yesterday i saw the 4th doctor since i am shot up and she gave me a new pill  olmesartan medoxomil,  only on it one day but my diastolic pressure is still much higher than before.  i dont want to die, i dont want a stroke, or a heart attach, i have a lot to live for still.  nobody is helping me, doctors are just throwing pills at me and not treating root cause which i feel strongly to beleive it is from covid shot.

I woke up on Sat April 17th the day after my 2nd dose of Moderna and went to the bathroom. I was sitting on toilet and next thin i know i'm waking up on the ground looking at the shower. I had blacked out. I then managed to pull myself up and was looking at the mirror in my bathroom and next thing i know i am waking up.  I had blacked out again.  My wife then discovered me on the floor and helped me up and to bed.  There is a cracked tile in my bathroom so i believe i knocked my head pretty good. I felt woozy and had a large scrape on  my right shoulder from one of the falls.  I was put into concussion protocol by wife;  The rest of the day i had the normal side effects of moderna: Fever, chills, headaches, sore left arm, and took tylenol extra strength, rested, hydrated, etc.  I felt better later in the day and by the next day Sunday April 18th i felt much  better;  I was able to drive and get errands done, but felt "Foggy".  I felt back to 100% maybe by Tuesday April 20th.  My concern is the blackouts not being known. If someone was operating heavy machinery or driving the day after their 2nd shot and blacked out that is a major cause for alarm.
LAB_DATA: i have not contacted my primary care physician about this at the time of this reporting and therefore have no further test or lab results.  i have recovered completely so I believe i will not bother getting any tests.

About 12 hours after the vaccine I had typical flu-like symptoms (fever, chills, etc..) for 2 days and then I felt back to normal.  A month later when I was about to start my menstrual cycle I developed the same symptoms which have never happened during that time of the month. I would usually feel a little fatigue and general discomfort but this time I got really sick with chills, body ache, nausea, dizziness, just as I did immediately after the shot.  It may not be related but I just wanted to report it in case someone else had the same problem.  It was just strange that in all my years of having a cycle that has never happened before.

Around 6 pm or so I started feeling chilled, the back of my neck hurt and I felt strange. By nighttime, I was having bad bad chills. My body was shaking uncontrollable because I was so cold. My body felt like it was made out of old rusty bolts with dagger ends and when I moved pain would shoot to different parts of my body, and my eyes hurt when I moved them. Normally, I run around playing hide n seek and freeze tag with my grandkids. But last night, I had to take 2 extra strength Excedrin, put lots of warm clothes on, and go to bed. After a while, my body stopped shaking and the Excedrin was taking the body hurts away. The next morning, April 22, I wasn't having chills or pains, but my body was still didn't feel normal. I felt so so tired, fatigued and my head hurt some. I had to go back to bed because I was so tired. I just got up around 5 pm and my body doesn't feel so tired. I feel better. I don't feel 100%, but much better, Thank God!
Pt 17 years old inadvertently given a COVID-19 vaccine, Moderna.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: MODERNA COVID 19 vaccination applied around 2:30 pm  that later after more or less 30 minutes from the application of vaccine started to feel breathing difficulty, mild cough and presented reddish discoloration on facial region. Patient also attempted to talk and her voice was almost gone. Patient was taken to the acute room by MA who applied the vaccine and  providers were notified about the emergency (3:00 pm aprox) , patient  was placed on semi Fowler position ( unable to tolerate complete supine position) due to  worsening of breathing difficulty; vital signs were taken,   O2 sat: 98%, pulse: : 74 X minute; BP: 150/90 Hg mm; oxygen applied through nasal cannula 4 L/min; patient referred also that she felt  that her  forehead was swollen and that she had blurry vision; reddish discoloration was observed on her face. 3:05 PM patient received epinephrine shot (0.5 mL IM STAT) on the lateral aspect of her left thigh; called rescue (around 3:07 PM) . After a minute of Epinephrine application patient refers feeling that she was breathing better. At 3:15 PM BP was taken again reporting 160/90 Hg mm; pulse was 82; reddish on face disappeared. Patient referred feeling improving not only regarding breathing but also on facial swelling sensation and also referred that her vision was not blurry anymore. Patient continue on oxygen source and around 3:18  pm rescue arrived. Rescue checked on patient and asked her if she wanted to go to the Hospital and patient answered : "No, I don't want to go to the Hospital". Patient signed  a refusal of treatment form, remained a few minutes more with oxygen, Oxygen was removed and saturation was assessed again reporting 98%; patient refers feeling well. Patient was accompanied by employee to the door and was picked up by relative and gone from the center. Patient left the Center feeling completely fine, denied difficulty breathing, CP, or any other symptoms.

I believe I experienced multiple symptoms as a result of my vaccine. My experience matches exactly as described in the article.  ON 4/1/21 at approximately 4pm I awoke from a nap experiencing acute vertigo, nausea and headache. I also was experiencing fever and chills. I began treating with excedrine but did not have an effect. The vertigo was very acute, my eyes were skipping and I was unable to walk. Nause was so intense that any attempt to leave my bed resulted in vomiting. I was unable to eat and could barely drink for the first 24 hours. Friday 4/2 at approx 7pm I took a dose of Promethazine which began to help the nausea. Extreme headache/migraine lasted for 3 days. During this time I also experienced extreme neck pain, as well as pain near base of skull, behind my ears, and on my temples. Symptoms were steadily improving each day, so I did not seek medical care during this time. I feel I became fully recovered by 4/18. I just had my second vaccine dose on 4/21 and I am very nervous about experiencing a relapse of symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Bloody nose, happened after I sneezed after I woke up from a nap, pretty heavy blood flow and didn?t stop, started coming out of both nostrils. The left nosebleed kept going but the right nose bleed stopped after a little while. Kept on bleeding for maybe 8 to 10 minutes as I cooked lunch, I plugged the nostril with a paper towel until it clotted three or four times but the flow still didn?t stop. I used to have nose bleeds frequently when I was a young child but don?t really have them often anymore. After plugging it with a paper towel was not successful, I tried pinching my nose bridge and leaning forward which worked a little bit better but I could tell that the flow hadn?t stopped because the blood and the bloody mucus would collect in my throat and I had to spit it out. I applied a Vaseline like jelly balm in order to moisturize the skin in my nostrils. About maybe around half an hour after my nose bleed started the flow has abated and I am able to do my tasks without having to spit out the bloody clotted mucus that slides into my mouth and throat. I think I have only had a few nose bleeds that I can remember that were as bad as this, probably only two or three. I ate lunch and did not notice a change in my perception of taste. Currently experiencing a very mild headache.

After vaccine, immediately I  felt a swoosh in my head and my left eye felt like it had gotten bigger. After leaving, I started having a slight headache. The headache got worst, and I took migraine med, fiorect, tylenol allergy sinus headache. By the time I laid down, my left leg was tingling and achy and I had to keep moving it because it was so restless, my whole arm down to my fingers was aching. The next morning I was better, but the headache continued. Friday afternoon, my left arm started hurting me with the pin and needles down to my fingers, the left side of my head was aching, and the side of my face. My tongue also felt funny and my eye was still hurting from when it felt like it had gotten bigger initially from the vaccine. It got worse, so early Saturday morning, I went to ER. The doctor said it was a side effect of the vaccine and it would go away in a few days, but she could give me something for the headache, I went for a follow-up with my neurologist this past Tuesday, and told her I was better, but my head was still hurting, so she gave me a shot for migraine. Today, I still have the tingling in my left arm to the tip of my fingers. I will follow up  with my Dr for the pain.

The patient is a 35 y/o African American female who presented today to the Vaccination Center for her first Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination. At approximately 3:45pm, she underwent her first shot. Given her history of MS, she had a medical consult and was sitting in the 15 minute waiting area.  About 10 minutes into her waiting time, she started to report chest tightness and heaviness.  She was transferred to the AED room and was placed on the cot for further evaluation. Past Medical History significant for asthma, GERD, MS.  She reports history of COVID in September 2020 at which time she developed anxiety and hypertension.  She was prescribed amlodipine at that time, but never started it. Denied history of stroke, heart attack, denied history of anaphylaxis. Denied shortness of breath.  Endorses anxiety after and leading up to vaccine. On Exam: Alert and oriented x3, responding appropriately to commands. VS: BP 180/110, HR 101, RR-20, O2 100% on RA.  Lungs bilaterally CTA, no wheezes or stridor, no angioedema. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my first shot on April 6th, 2021, and on April 18th, 2021 I experienced extreme numbness with slight pain in the fold and shoulder of my arm. I went to the ER and they took a cat scan of my neck and reported back that everything looked normal - the nurse said it was most likely Cervical Radiculopathy. Then the following morning around 11 AM, I experienced very intense burning in my chest starting on the right side, eventually moving to the left encompassing my entire upper chest. I also experienced a very bad migraine, which I am typically used to but this one was more of a pressure headache between my temples that I felt in my ears and jaw. I made the decision to go back to the ER and to a different one this time. The ER failed to administer a Covid-19 test and to take bloodwork - both faults that family and friends in the medical field have pointed out to me. The doctor there had me receive an IV, a chest X-Ray, and an EKG. The X-Ray and EKG were both normal. The doctor had ordered a Covid-19 test but the nurse forgot to administer it before my discharge. In my IV I received Benadryl and Reglan along with typical IV fluids. I was also given Pepcid and Mylanta. At the end of my visit, the doctor concluded that he thought it was my acid reflux acting up - gastroenteritis. I went home and continued to experience chest burning, tightness, occasional numbness/pains in my body, and very, very bad headaches. On top of that, I could barely swallow - it felt as if my throat was closing. I took Pepcid and Tums and neither really did anything. After seeing a Cardiologist this same week, they ordered an Echocardiogram and routine bloodwork (metabolic panel). I will also be following up with a GI, and I received a Covid-19 test today and am awaiting the results. It is possible I contracted Covid before my shot, but it is also possible that I am having a delayed reaction to my first vaccination as well. Who knows.
LAB_DATA: Cat Scan of the Neck (4/19/21 @ ~4 AM), EKG (4/19/21 @ ~2 PM), Chest X-Ray (4/19/21 @ ~6 PM), EKG (4/20/21 @ ~4 PM), Metabolic Panel bloodwork (4/21/21 @ ~215 PM), and Covid-19 test (4/22/21 @ ~12PM).

The day following the vaccination, I had a fever, intense chills, and a mild headache. I have had an upset stomach since the second vaccination, with intermittent stomach pain.   Last night (04/22/2021, starting around 7:30 PM), I had intense lower abdominal pain, loose stool, vomiting, and an intense chill. The symptoms came on suddenly (over the period of a half hour). After vomiting, I was seized by sudden, intense, lower-back pain immediately followed by full-body tremors. The tremors started with my legs, then went to my hands and finally my arms. I have never had a problem with tremors or seizures before. The back pain and tremors fully subsided after 10 minutes.   I did not visit a doctor, since it is doubtful that they would definitively blame the Covid vaccine, and I would be stuck with a large hospital bill. However, the symptoms were too peculiar to be attributed to a random illness. I do believe they are a side effect from the second vaccine dose.  This morning I feel tired and am a pound lighter, but I am quickly recovering.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Feb. 15, 10:45 pm - Noticed muscle ache in upper thoracic spine area. Took tylenol Feb. 16, 6:00 am - Woke up to same muscle ache, now in general thoracic spine area.                                   Alternated btwn tylenol/ibuprofen  q, 4-6 hrs. Feb. 16, 7:00pm - Same discomfort in back, but now progressing to my left side. Feb. 17, 2 pm - Discomfort now progressing from spine to left side to left, front chest. Muscle ache                            and slight pressure at left chest. Tylenol/ibuprofen  q, 4-6 hrs. Feb. 18, 3 am - Woke up w/ more muscle ache & pressure in left chest area FEB. 18: 8:30 am - Went to Urgent Care-Sent to Hospital. Admitted for observation, more tests. FEB 19: Seen by Internist, who ruled out any cardiac problems. Wondered if the line of pain/discomfort could be precursor to Shingles, with activation of Herpes Zoster as a result of 2nd Covid-19 vaccine. Back area examined and no presence of rash noticed. Ordered MRI of thoracic spine. FEB. 19, afternoon: Discharged to home - MRI nonsignificant FEB. 20: 8:30am - Presence of red rash, in a continuous band from thoracic spine around left side to left chest, circling 2inches up on sternum. FEB 20: 10am - Confirmation of Herpes Zoster/Shingles at Urgent Care.  Put on Valacyclovir (x3/day for 10 days); HYDROcodone-acetaminophen (5-325 mg/tablet q. 6hr PRN); Ibuprofen (600mg q.6hr PRN) MAR. 1 - Office visit - continue w/ meds MAR. 9 - Messaged Dr. that neuralgia pain worsening albeit rash subsiding. Lidocaine suggested, continued w/ PRN meds. Mar 17 - Neuralgia pain intensifying from spine, left to sternum, no relief from above meds.  Put on: Gabapentin 100 mg x2/day. March 25 - Severe Neuralgia pain-Dr. increased dose to 200 mg x3/day. April 5 - Neuralgia pain subsiding, gabapentin lowered to 100 mg x2/day.  Today, April 21 - Gabapentin continues to be taken at 100 mg x2/day.
LAB_DATA: Feb. 18: EKG 12-Lead (sinus tachycardia, nonspecific ST abnormality) Feb. 18: TSH w/o reflex,T4 Free, Troponin (x3), Lipase, Comp. Metabolic Panel, CBC w/ Diff; ALL WNL. FEB 18: D-Dimer, Quantitative: 405 value.  XR Chest 1 View and CTA Chest with Contrast: Nonacute chest,  no evidence of pulm. artery embolism or other acute cardiopulmonary process. NM Myocardial SPECT Rx - normal Cardiac Stress Test - normal MRI showed no fracture/dislocation or significant stenosis with mild degenerative changes.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had my first vaccine (Moderna, V00120) on February 26. About a week after,  I started feeling paresthesia, numbness in the right side of my body, specifically in the right leg and arm, and I started having difficulties walking.  Since the symptoms persisted, I went to the Dr. on March 23. I told him that I thought my symptom were out of the blue and I linked them to the vaccine, so I was visiting him to see if I should put my second vaccine in those circumstances, few days after. Doctor said that there was no relation between nerve damage and the vaccine and he recommended me to put it.  He sent me test thinking that could be multiple esclerosis. I did my brain MRI on Thursday 25 and on Friday March 26 I put my second dose.  About a week after the second dose my symptoms  were dramatically aggravated. I first started experiencing  a sudden fatigue that didn't even allow me to hold the cellphone or a spoon and I had to lie down. I couldn't hold my 8 months daughter because I felt such a strong weakness. This fatigue didn't allow me to work. This happened few days in a raw for few hours. On April 8th I started to feel needles and strong neuropathic pain that I had never experience in my whole life. On April 9th in the evening I had a massive crisis. I started to feel a sudden  having a lot of cold, starting shivering and then chattering teeth and strong headache. (Same reaction I had 12 hours after putting the second dose of the vaccine).  I had to lie down in bed and my husband had to cover me with a jumper and eiderdown, but I still was cold. I couldn't stop shivering. Then I had difficulty swallowing. And the worst part started when I felt all over my body an intense pins and needles, burning, electricity, very profoundly and spread all over in a very intense way., I thought I was dying. I started panicking, I didn't have control over my body. I had difficulty breathing and such a weakness that didn't make me speak because I couldn't stop chattering my teeth. Was the worst life experience ever until that moment. The situation lasted about 90 minutes and then went away. The next day, Sunday April 10th, I spent the whole day in bed to rest, but at night time I experienced the same crisis as the night before. It started with the sudden cold as well.  After that I didn't have more crises but the pins and needles pain remains and it made it difficult to sleep because of the pain and discomfort and I wonder if I would have it my entire life. I returned to the doctor. To a different one specialized in multiple esclerosis. Brain MRI came out negative but it was done one day before the second dose, so we cannot be sure. I did 3 MRI of my whole spine and some muscular tests to check the response of the nerves. They also took 8 tubes of blood. We are waiting for the results but doctor think is Guillain Barrel syndrome. She thinks I am suffering peripheral neuropathy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt reports she was in Hospital until 2 days ago when she received 2nd Moderna COVID vaccine. She states that several hours later she began feeling globally weak and with coordination difficulties intermittently (gives example that she would be feeding self, then have difficulty getting utensil to mouth and noted sudden collapse of LE when standing, "they just gave out" and feels that difficulty coordinating her legs led to inability to stand- adamant that it is coordination rather than fatigue or weakness at issue). She feels symptoms in extremities are bilateral and symmetric. Denies prodrome prior to falls, denies LOC but states she fell onto her face and did not "catch" herself "it happened too fast". She has been able to ambulate with assistance to bathroom and in her house in recent days. Denies paresthesias, numbness to groin or perineum. She has been constipated, which is new for her with last BM 4/17 no GIB. Pt denies dysuria or difficulties with urination, though she tells me she has not voided since yesterday. She states she has been eating without n/v or early satiety. No change in chronic cough or DOE. She has not had fevers or chills,  denies myalgias or arthralgias.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: No adverse event. Spacing was error 1st dose was 3/22.

Patient does not remember most of the adverse event. Patient's partner reports that patient started feeling a tingling sensation on his left arm about 10 minutes after vaccination. Partner also reports that patient was hallucinating and sending her confusing text messages during his 15 minute observation period. The patient did not report feeling any adverse symptoms at the checkout station after his 15 minute observation period and before leaving the vaccination clinic.    After patient returned home, his partner reports considerable swelling on his left arm, continued hallucinations and trying to dismiss her concerns. Subsequently, that same day, partner reports the patient had a severe migrane and began to lose feeling on his left arm and leg, at which point the patient also lost consciousness.  Also at this point, the partner calls 911.   After arrival of emergency personnel, the patient regains consciousness, but does not remember name and complains of continued pain on his arm. He is transported to hospital where he spends 3 nights and receives treatment and care for stroke symptoms.    Patient reports that he does not remember much of anything 1.5 days after vaccination.   After returning home from hospital, patient complains of memory lapses and begins seeing neurologist for minor seizures during his sleep.   Wife reports that patient now lashes out and easily loses temper due to the fact that his memory is foggy.
HISTORY: congenital heart condition, multiple heart surgeries, pacemaker

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient presented for her second COVID vaccine on 04/21/21 and described events following her first vaccine on 03/24/21. She reported that about 30 minutes after her vaccine she felt the vaccine "moving through her arm". She stated her left arm, hand, and fingers were tingling all the way up to her neck.  She did not feel short of breath but did report that her tongue felt "thick".  She also reported that her brain was "foggy" and she had a metallic taste in her mouth.  These sensations lasted throughout the day and evening and she was "fine" the next day.  She did not discuss any of her symptoms with a doctor. She states she had hesitations about getting the second vaccine. We discussed that due to her side effects we would not recommend getting the second vaccine at this time and that she could discuss further with her primary care if needed. She was agreeable to this.

Reason for admission: Present on Admission: o Pulmonary emboli  .Hospital Course: 84-year-old male past medical history of CAD status post CABG, hypertension, obesity, COPD and hyperlipidemia.  TTE back in fall 2020 had noted severe aortic stenosis with a normal ejection fraction.  Heart catheterization and 9/10/2020 showed severe native vessel CAD.  Occluded saphenous vein graft to the circumflex, occluded saphenous vein graft to the RPDA.  Distal RCA fills retrograde collaterals from the distal circumflex. TTE from 10/20/2020 with an EF of 60%, abnormal LV diastolicDysfunction, mildly dilated ascending aorta and mild MR.  There is mild perivalvular regurgitation with a mean gradient of 15 mmHg. He had the Johnson & Johnson COVID-19 vaccination on 3/17/2021.  Rapid Covid test was negative.  High-sensitivity troponin was elevated at 276.  CT of the chest showed bilateral pulmonary emboli most pronounced on the right.  EKG showed sinus rhythm with right bundle branch block and ST depression was noted. He was transition to warfarin, he is unable to take NOAC due to Dilantin history.  INR was slowly increased to 3 mg.  He was discharged with Lovenox bridge with plans to have INR checked on Wednesday or Thursday at the Hospital and he will follow-up with his PCP for management. Patient was admitted to the hospital on 4/13/2021.  Patient reported she noticed return of the rest pain to the left lower extremity starting on 4/12/2021.  Patient was found to have acute on chronic limb ischemia of the LLE and was found to have an occluded left femoropopliteal bypass graft.  She was taken to the OR on 4/14/2021 and underwent a thrombectomy and removal of distal portion of the graft, which appeared to be infected.  Cultures from the left femoral thrombus was positive for gram-negative rods.  Blood cultures from 4/13/2021 were positive for Pseudomonas aeruginosa.  Postoperatively, her left lower extremity continue to be numb, cool, and she was unable to dorsiflex the foot.  Patient ultimately underwent a left lower extremity below the knee amputation on 4/16/2021.  Patient remains hospitalized at this time.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have chronic, constant, and moderate (6 using a 0-10 scale with 10 most painful) osteoarthritis in both left and right knee joints, in part associated with prior knee reconstruction 20-years ago. I had the same unexpected event following dose-1 and dose-2 of the Pfizer SARS-C0V-2 vaccine. In both vaccination events the unexpected effect persisted for 72 hours post-vaccine delivery. Following each vaccine dose I had near complete relief from chronic pain in both knees. I had no detrimental adverse events associated with the vaccine (no injection site soreness, no fever, no fatigue, etc ...). However, the loss of pain and gain of range of movement in both knees despite the progressive osteoarthritis was marked. These seem like anti-inflammatory responses, which also seems counter to the immune systems response to the mRNA-derived antigen. After 72-hours the pain relief and range of motion returned to pre-vaccination levels without further incidence. I would be curious if any of the "inert" components (or the lipid NPs) of the vaccine have any prior indication of beneficial adjuvant use. The pain management gains were consistent and comparable between dose-1 and dose-2 of the Vx.
LAB_DATA: No additional medical intervention was required.
HISTORY: Moderate to advanced osteoarthritis in left and right knee joints

My daughter has been diagnosed with catamenial epilepsy, and typically only had seizures very sporadically (months apart).  However, she recently had a cluster of seizures, which was very atypical for her.  I read a news story last night about the vaccine affecting some women by making their period come back after years of not having it.  In reviewing my daughter's seizure events, a pattern emerged in relation to her Covid shots:  -Dose 1 of Pfizer on March 17, and the worst seizure she ever had was on March 27 (10 days after first Covid shot) -Dose 2 of Pfizer on March 31, and the second worst seizure she ever had was on April 10 (10 days after second Covid shot)  Prior to the Pfizer Covid shots, the shortest frequency between seizures was one month, and that was prior to her starting epilepsy medication (Keppra).  She was taking her Keppra (morning and night) at 1000 mg twice daily as prescribed, and had not missed any doses when the seizures occurred.  We now suspect that the two recent seizures might be adverse reactions to the Covid shots.
